  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink262-kilavi">varaintukoḷḷa niṉaikkilaṉ eṉṟu vēṟupaṭṭa talaimakaḷ avaṉ niṉmēl viruppamuṭaiyavaṉ nī nōkiṉṟatu eṉṉai’ eṉṟa tōḻikkuc colliyatu.
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">What the heroine told the confidante; the heroine who differed, saying, “He does not think to marry [me],” to the confidante who said, “He has desire for you; why do you suffer?”
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink262">
<l>ciṟutiṉai mēynta taṟukaṭ paṉṟi</l>
<l>tuṟuka laṭukkattut tuṇaiyoṭu vatiyu</l>
<l>milaṅkumalai nāṭaṉ varūu</l>
<l>maruntu maṟiyuṅko ṟōḻiyavaṉ viruppē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>The man from the land of the shining hills,</l>
        <l>where cruel boars that graze upon small millet,</l>
        <l>live with their companions</l>
        <l>on the mountain slopes with thick stones,</l>
        <l rend="space">will come. </l>
        <l rend="space indent">But does his longing know</l>
        <l rend="indent">the medicine (i.e., marriage)</l>
        <l rend="indent">[for my suffering], O friend?</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
